00:02:21.270 --> 00:02:23.530
kind of our starting point.

00:02:23.530 --> 00:02:26.980
So like I said, we're going to
jump through a couple of

00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:30.000
different steps and along the
way, we'll talk about what is

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:33.550
involved in each step and
how to actually do it.

00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:38.480
So the first step is to change
to the Holo theme, and add an

00:02:38.480 --> 00:02:40.150
action bar to your app.

00:02:40.150 --> 00:02:43.630
So you can see here that the
Holo theme-- actually, the

00:02:43.630 --> 00:02:46.120
Holo theme automatically gives
you an action bar by default.

00:02:46.120 --> 00:02:48.990
But you have the action bar at
the top, and what that gives

00:02:48.990 --> 00:02:51.800
you is that gives you a sense of
place into where you are in

00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:54.020
the app and which app you're
in-- so you see the little

00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:55.300
icon here--

00:02:55.300 --> 00:02:58.370
as well as some basic actions
that are immediately

00:02:58.370 --> 00:02:59.270
available on screen.

00:02:59.270 --> 00:03:01.500
So things like refresh, if you
wanted to be able to refresh

00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:05.010
the list of articles, as well
as an overflow, giving you

00:03:05.010 --> 00:03:08.240
access to things that usually
you would see under the legacy

00:03:08.240 --> 00:03:10.460
menu button.

00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:13.830
ADAM KOCH: And just from a
developer standpoint, it's

00:03:13.830 --> 00:03:16.820
really a matter of enabling a
target SDK version for your

00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:20.070
application in your manifest of,
I think, 11 or above, but

00:03:20.070 --> 00:03:22.580
obviously, we recommend
targeting the latest platform

00:03:22.580 --> 00:03:24.430
version where you can.

00:03:24.430 --> 00:03:26.390
So in this case, we just put
down here a little note that

00:03:26.390 --> 00:03:31.160
says target SDK version of 17.

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:35.630
And in addition, there's a theme
that you can set for

00:03:35.630 --> 00:03:38.620
Holo, so in this case, it's
Theme.Holo Light Dark Action

00:03:38.620 --> 00:03:41.420
Bar, so that's the light theme
down bottom, with a dark

00:03:41.420 --> 00:03:43.930
action bar at the top.

00:03:43.930 --> 00:03:46.085
NICK BUTCHER: And one really
little thing to pick out here

00:03:46.085 --> 00:03:47.870
is if you take a look at the
background color on here, you

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:50.010
see it's changed from pretty
much pure white to a slightly

00:03:50.010 --> 00:03:53.370
off white, which is part of
the Holo palette really.

00:03:53.370 --> 00:03:56.030
And there's really good reasons
that we selected these

00:03:56.030 --> 00:03:58.390
base colors for the base themes
which you inherit from,

00:03:58.390 --> 00:04:01.500
because that white on mobile
can be a searingly bright

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:04.140
color, which you want to use
quite sparingly, and it's not

00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:05.770
very great for the
background color.

00:04:05.770 --> 00:04:09.230
So it's a subtle change, but
it instantly makes the app

00:04:09.230 --> 00:04:10.820
easier to read.

00:04:10.820 --> 00:04:11.530
ROMAN NURIK: For sure.

00:04:11.530 --> 00:04:14.170
And we've kept that throughout,
so you'll see the

00:04:14.170 --> 00:04:16.810
evolution of this design with
more branding elements and

00:04:16.810 --> 00:04:20.320
things like that, and we've
kept that default color.

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:21.010
So let's move on.

00:04:21.010 --> 00:04:21.700
What's the next step?

00:04:21.700 --> 00:04:24.230
We have an action bar, we
have the Holo theme.

00:04:24.230 --> 00:04:26.640
That gives you a little bit,
that improves the visual

00:04:26.640 --> 00:04:28.990
design a little bit, but
what's the next step?

00:04:28.990 --> 00:04:31.980
So the next step is to customize
the action bar and

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:35.680
give your app a little
touch of branding.

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:38.670
So you'll see here that
we've chosen an

00:04:38.670 --> 00:04:39.840
orange color palette.

00:04:39.840 --> 00:04:41.510
And again, this is
really up to you.

00:04:41.510 --> 00:04:44.810
If you have an existing service,
an existing color

00:04:44.810 --> 00:04:47.360
scheme for your brand,
introduce it.

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:50.290
This is the best place, I'd say,
in your app to introduce

00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:54.050
branding, is the action bar
since it's a key structural

00:04:54.050 --> 00:04:56.940
element, yet at the same time,
it's a key area to

00:04:56.940 --> 00:04:58.640
differentiate.

00:04:58.640 --> 00:05:01.500
And then the little icon we
chose here, this is actually

00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:03.030
not a standard launcher icon.

00:05:03.030 --> 00:05:06.160
This is a custom icon
for the action bar.

00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:08.960
And so remember that you don't
necessarily have to have your

00:05:08.960 --> 00:05:12.210
exact pixel for pixel launcher
icon in the action bar.

00:05:12.210 --> 00:05:16.110
You can customize it so that it
looks good in the context

00:05:16.110 --> 00:05:17.190
of the action bar.

00:05:17.190 --> 00:05:20.330
And so the launcher icon for
this app would probably be an

00:05:20.330 --> 00:05:23.870
orange circle with a white y,
but we decided that this

00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:26.540
inverted color scheme would
look good here.

00:05:26.540 --> 00:05:31.820
And you'll also notice that
we've introduced some of the

00:05:31.820 --> 00:05:36.160
same color scheme elements
throughout the content.

00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:38.120
By the way, I should
preface that.

