00:17:15.130 --> 00:17:16.380
So let's jump into tablet.

00:17:18.800 --> 00:17:21.920
Let's take a flashback
to our Step Zero.

00:17:21.920 --> 00:17:24.510
If you were to run that Step
Zero starting point on a

00:17:24.510 --> 00:17:26.319
tablet, this is what
it would look like.

00:17:26.319 --> 00:17:28.950
So you'd have two separate
screens that just make

00:17:28.950 --> 00:17:30.080
horrible use of space.

00:17:30.080 --> 00:17:33.130
You have all these large regions
of white space here at

00:17:33.130 --> 00:17:34.920
the bottom.

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:36.740
You also very large
line lengths--

00:17:36.740 --> 00:17:38.370
we'll talk about that--

00:17:38.370 --> 00:17:40.490
which makes reading
really a pain.

00:17:40.490 --> 00:17:44.620
So as you're reading the first
line here, here, here, here,

00:17:44.620 --> 00:17:46.600
then it's time to go on
to the next line.

00:17:46.600 --> 00:17:48.260
Your eye is trying to move to
the next line, but it's very

00:17:48.260 --> 00:17:52.550
hard for it to find the next
line, because this text has

00:17:52.550 --> 00:17:54.060
too long of a measure.

00:17:54.060 --> 00:17:56.540
So we'll talk about how
to improve that.

