00:19:20.050 --> 00:19:21.522
And you can read about
the details here in

00:19:21.522 --> 00:19:23.290
these training articles.

00:19:23.290 --> 00:19:25.460
So moving on.

00:19:25.460 --> 00:19:27.560
How would we then
improve this?

00:19:27.560 --> 00:19:32.360
So what we can do is now start
tweaking, again, the margins

00:19:32.360 --> 00:19:33.620
and the spacing and
the different

00:19:33.620 --> 00:19:35.980
dimensions on tablets.

00:19:35.980 --> 00:19:40.830
So that when you open up the
same detail view on a tablet,

00:19:40.830 --> 00:19:43.600
you'll actually get larger
text, for example.

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.980
You get more spacing on the
sides to, again, better

00:19:46.980 --> 00:19:49.790
separate the figure from the
ground, better separate the

00:19:49.790 --> 00:19:52.240
text from its background.

00:19:52.240 --> 00:19:53.750
You can bump up font sizes.

00:19:53.750 --> 00:19:55.930
You can bump up line spacing.

00:19:55.930 --> 00:19:58.710
Again, lots of things you can
do here to make it better.

00:19:58.710 --> 00:20:02.040
And it's fairly easy from the
development side as well.

00:20:02.040 --> 00:20:04.570
ADAM KOCH: I mean hopefully,
when we are talking about the

00:20:04.570 --> 00:20:08.320
phone side, you extracted all
of the different dimensions,

00:20:08.320 --> 00:20:12.800
padding, spacing, into a
separate XML file, and then

00:20:12.800 --> 00:20:15.710
you can choose when you want
to bump those up again, at

00:20:15.710 --> 00:20:16.960
which screen size you want
to bump them up.

