And again, this still uses the
48dp rhythm in the sense that

00:21:16.110 --> 00:21:20.550
things are generally multiples
of 48 or 16, and for smaller

00:21:20.550 --> 00:21:25.960
sizes, we use 32, 16, 24,
8, things like that.

00:21:25.960 --> 00:21:30.770
Powers of two and things
divisible by four, roughly.

00:21:30.770 --> 00:21:33.630
So here's just some of
the quick examples.

00:21:33.630 --> 00:21:36.510
Generous margins around
the content here.

