00:23:30.190 --> 00:23:34.660
So moving on, another quick
tidbit is if you're using a

00:23:34.660 --> 00:23:36.830
web view for presenting
content, then you're

00:23:36.830 --> 00:23:37.820
automatically going
to get this.

00:23:37.820 --> 00:23:40.470
But if you're not, if you're
using a text view, by default,

00:23:40.470 --> 00:23:42.200
your text will not
be selectable.

00:23:42.200 --> 00:23:45.600
So if you long press on
the body content,

00:23:45.600 --> 00:23:46.710
nothing will happen.

00:23:46.710 --> 00:23:49.510
So there's a really
neat little trick

00:23:49.510 --> 00:23:49.980
that you could do.

00:23:49.980 --> 00:23:52.870
You could set a single attribute
on your text view--

00:23:52.870 --> 00:23:54.450
and this is more for developers,
of course--

00:23:54.450 --> 00:23:56.410
that makes that text
selectable.

00:23:56.410 --> 00:23:58.440
And from there, you can
obviously customize.

00:23:58.440 --> 00:24:00.680
You can say, allow people
to share this text or

00:24:00.680 --> 00:24:01.556
copy it, and so on.

00:24:01.556 --> 00:24:02.710
ADAM KOCH: And surprise,
surprise.

00:24:02.710 --> 00:24:07.000
That attribute is called
Text Is Selectable.

00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:07.050
Easy.

00:24:07.050 --> 00:24:09.600
ROMAN NURIK: Very simple.

